## Lesson 6 - Control Flow and Loops

-- a while loop will repeat for as long as a condition is true
-- We can use a while loop to keep track of anything using the while/do syntax. You'll use the end keyword to close your loop.


# Negating State
In many game systems, you're constantly checking for when to stop doing something, which often depends on the absence of a state, not just its presence.

To negate state means to check if something is not true, using the keyword not.
